brands.description: The Print Shop is a basic desktop publishing software package developed in the early 1980s by Brøderbund. It was unique in that it provided libraries of clip-art and templates through a simple interface to build signs, posters and banners with household dot-matrix printers. Over the years the software has been updated to accommodate changing file formats and printer technologies.
brands.name: The Print Shop

brands.description: Promotional merchandise, promotional items, promotional products, promotional gifts, or advertising gifts, sometimes nicknamed swag, are articles of merchandise (often branded with a logo or slogan) used in marketing and communication programs. They are given away to promote a company, corporate image, brand, or event at trade shows, conferences, and as part of guerrilla marketing campaigns.

transcript.text: Hello and welcome to on Print Shop.
In today's video, we are excited to introduce the Advanced Finishes feature in the Designer Studio module.
This feature adds a touch of luxury, durability, and unique customization to printed products.
Customers can now enhance their designs with effects such as spot UV emboss, deboss, and raised foil.
The process of adding these effects is straightforward and consistent across all options.
In this video, we'll demonstrate the spot UV effect added to a design template.
Let's get started with the Designer Studio.
While designing a template, users can select any object and a quick action pop up will offer the option to apply the spot UV effect.
Once applied, the effect is reflected in real time and can be viewed in the 3D preview box.
To examine the effect more closely, expand the preview screen and rotate the product at different angles.
For example, you'll notice a shining effect applied to the logo on both pages.
Additionally, the Finishes option in the top panel allows users to apply these effects to multiple elements and pages simultaneously, streamlining the process.
Now, let's explore how these finishing options can be enabled.
In the Admin panel, navigate to the Designer Studio module, click on Studio Settings and search for Spot.
To activate the Spot UV coating finish, enable the corresponding setting.
Similarly, you can activate the raised foil emboss and Deboss effects from the Studio settings for a visually appealing result.
Assign appropriate 3D models to the products from the real preview section, and this will be all about the Advanced Finishes feature.
These advanced finishes elevate product designs, offering a premium look and feel to meet diverse customer needs.
Thank you for watching, and we look forward to seeing how these updates help enhance your business operations.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help, just reach out through live chat on on Printshop.
Com Thanks for tuning in.
